There is no way to Create, Update or Delete additional user property via Jira SOAP Service (e.g. JiraSoapService etc).

I am trying to use this functionality when trying to import or update additional user info from LDAP to Jira using Jira web services. (e.g. 'Telephone number', 'Title' (job position) etc etc)

I didn't found even a patch for this as there is one already provided when exposing an user update functionality in http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-11252

The jira form template sets the submit button id like this:
{noformat}
<input type="submit" name="<decorator:getProperty property="submitName" />" id="<decorator:getProperty property="submitName" />" value="<decorator:getProperty property="submitName" />"
{noformat}

This means the id of the button will change depending on the user's locale which makes the 'id' pretty useless if you're trying to select the button via javascript!

